MechanicalUI
  
Natural Electronic Input: (http://www.pages.drexel.edu/~pb762/000_0462.JPG)

USE ONE TYPE FOR EACH PURPOSE TO OFFER FAMILIARITY

fundamental:
  Button [widget]
    input - boolean, squarewidth
    display - [ submit ]
    
  Switch [widget]
    input - boolean, squarewidth
    output - boolean
    display - [_] [X]
    
  Light [widget]
    output - boolean, squarewidth
    display - {X}
    
  Slider [widget]
    input - 0..1 float, squarewidth
    display - [--|-------]

  Bar [widget]
    output - 0..1 float, squarewidth
    display - {--|-------}

  Text [widget]
    output - text, squarewidth
    display - {HELLO WORL}

ideas:
  Static Text / Images (labels etc)       HELLO WORLD
  Dead Switch (Slide lock?)               [>>>>>-----]
  Switches (multi state)                  [_][X][_][_]
  Groupings                             |--TITLE---|
                                        |>content  |
                                        |----------|
  Screen placement with memory (lsdj)   [A][B][*][D]
  Wire connections (x->x)               >TEXT< [ ]---->[ ] >TEXT<
                                        >TEXT< [ ]\    [ ] >TEXT<
                                        >TEXT< [ ] \   [ ] >TEXT<
                                        >TEXT< [ ]  \  [ ] >TEXT<
                                        >TEXT< [ ]   \ [ ] >TEXT<
                                        >TEXT< [ ]    >[ ] >TEXT<
  Number Counter                        [00000102[+-]]
